246 /*========== Static Function Implementations ================================*/
247 static bool MRC_MeasurementUpdatedAtLeastOnce(uint32_t timestamp, uint32_t previousTimestamp) {
248  bool retval = false;
249  if (!((timestamp == 0u) && (previousTimestamp == 0u))) {
250  /* Only possibility for timestamp AND previous timestamp to be 0 is, if
251  the measurement has never been updated. Thus, if this is not the case
252  the measurement must have been updated */
253  retval = true;
254  }
255  return retval;
256 }
257 
258 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e MRC_MeasurementUpdatedRecently(
259  uint32_t timestamp,
260  uint32_t previousTimestamp,
261  uint32_t timeInterval) {
262  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e retval = STD_NOT_OK;
263  uint32_t currentTimestamp = OS_GetTickCount();
264 
265  /* Unsigned integer arithmetic also works correctly if currentTimestamp is
266  larger than pHeader->timestamp (timer overflow), thus no need to use abs() */
267  if (((currentTimestamp - timestamp) <= timeInterval) &&
268  (MRC_MeasurementUpdatedAtLeastOnce(timestamp, previousTimestamp) == true)) {
269  /* Difference between current timestamp and last update timestamp is
270  smaller than passed time interval */
271  retval = STD_OK;
272  }
273  return retval;
274 }

276 static bool MRC_ValidateCellVoltageMeasurement(
277  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_VOLTAGE_s *pCellVoltageBase,
278  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_VOLTAGE_s *pCellVoltageRedundancy0) {
279  FAS_ASSERT(pCellVoltageBase != NULL_PTR);
280  FAS_ASSERT(pCellVoltageRedundancy0 != NULL_PTR);
281 
282  bool updatedValidatedVoltageDatbaseEntry = false;
283 
284  bool baseCellVoltageUpdated = false;
285 
286  bool useCellVoltageRedundancy = false;
287  bool baseCellVoltageMeasurementTimeoutReached = true;
288  bool redundancy0CellVoltageMeasurementTimeoutReached = true;
289 
290  /* Following decision will be undertaken:
291  *
292  * - Use redundancy only if timestamp of redundant database entry != 0
293  * - Perform redundant check if both timestamps have been updated
294  * - Add timeout and trigger error if timestamps have not been updated in the last XXXXms
295  * - If timeout reached and only one of the two redundant measurements has been updated use this measurement value
296  * but throw an error that one measurement has not been updated recently.
297  */
298 
299  /* -------------- Check if cell voltage redundant measurement is used -- */
300  /* Use redundant cell voltage measurements if measurement values have been acquired once */
301  useCellVoltageRedundancy = DATA_DatabaseEntryUpdatedAtLeastOnce(pCellVoltageRedundancy0->header);
302 
303  /* ----------------- Check timestamp of base measurements--------------- */
304  if (DATA_EntryUpdatedWithinInterval(pCellVoltageBase->header, MRC_AFE_MEASUREMENT_PERIOD_TIMEOUT_ms) == true) {
305  baseCellVoltageMeasurementTimeoutReached = false;
306  (void)DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_BASE_CELL_VOLTAGE_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_EVENT_OK, DIAG_SYSTEM, 0u);
307  } else {
308  baseCellVoltageMeasurementTimeoutReached = true;
309  /* Set error flag */
310  (void)DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_BASE_CELL_VOLTAGE_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_EVENT_NOT_OK, DIAG_SYSTEM, 0u);
311  }
312 
313  /* Check if base measurement values have been updated since last MRC */
314  if (mrc_state.lastBaseCellVoltageTimestamp != pCellVoltageBase->header.timestamp) {
315  baseCellVoltageUpdated = true;
316  } else {
317  baseCellVoltageUpdated = false;
318  }
319 
320  /* ----------------- Check timestamp of redundant measurements --------- */
321  if ((DATA_EntryUpdatedWithinInterval(pCellVoltageRedundancy0->header, MRC_AFE_MEASUREMENT_PERIOD_TIMEOUT_ms) ==
322  false) &&
323  (useCellVoltageRedundancy == true)) {
324  redundancy0CellVoltageMeasurementTimeoutReached = true;
325  /* Set error flag */
326  (void)DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_REDUNDANCY0_CELL_VOLTAGE_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_EVENT_NOT_OK, DIAG_SYSTEM, 0u);
327  } else {
328  redundancy0CellVoltageMeasurementTimeoutReached = false;
329  (void)DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_REDUNDANCY0_CELL_VOLTAGE_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_EVENT_OK, DIAG_SYSTEM, 0u);
330  }
331 
332  /* ----------------- Validate cell voltages ---------------------------- */
333  if (useCellVoltageRedundancy == true) {
334  bool redundany0CellVoltageUpdated = false;
335  /* Check if redundant measurement values have been updated since last MRC */
336  if (mrc_state.lastRedundancy0CellVoltageTimestamp != pCellVoltageRedundancy0->header.timestamp) {
337  redundany0CellVoltageUpdated = true;
338  } else {
339  redundany0CellVoltageUpdated = false;
340  }
341  /* Make sure cell voltage timestamps have been updated since last call */
342  if ((baseCellVoltageUpdated == true) && (redundany0CellVoltageUpdated == true)) {
343  /* Update timestamp */
344  mrc_state.lastBaseCellVoltageTimestamp = pCellVoltageBase->header.timestamp;
345  mrc_state.lastRedundancy0CellVoltageTimestamp = pCellVoltageRedundancy0->header.timestamp;
346 
347  /* Validate cell voltages */
348  MRC_ValidateCellVoltage(pCellVoltageBase, pCellVoltageRedundancy0, &mrc_tableCellVoltages);
349  /* Set to true for following minimum, maximum and average calculation */
350  updatedValidatedVoltageDatbaseEntry = true;
351  } else if ((baseCellVoltageUpdated == true) || (redundany0CellVoltageUpdated == true)) {
352  /* At least one measurement has been updated */
353  if (baseCellVoltageUpdated == true) {
354  /* Has redundant measurement timeout been reached? If yes, update. */
355  if (redundancy0CellVoltageMeasurementTimeoutReached == true) {
356  /* Copy cell voltage base measurement values into validated database struct */
357  MRC_UpdateCellVoltageValidation(pCellVoltageBase, &mrc_tableCellVoltages);
358  /* Set to true for following minimum, maximum and average calculation */
359  updatedValidatedVoltageDatbaseEntry = true;
360  }
361  } else if (redundany0CellVoltageUpdated == true) {
362  /* Has base measurement timeout been reached? If yes, update. */
363  if (baseCellVoltageMeasurementTimeoutReached == true) {
364  /* Copy cell voltage base measurement values into validated database struct */
365  MRC_UpdateCellVoltageValidation(pCellVoltageRedundancy0, &mrc_tableCellVoltages);
366  /* Set to true for following minimum, maximum and average calculation */
367  updatedValidatedVoltageDatbaseEntry = true;
368  }
369  } else {
370  FAS_ASSERT(FAS_TRAP);
371  }
372  } else {
373  /* No cell voltage measurement has been updated -> do nothing */
374  }
375  } else {
376  if (baseCellVoltageUpdated == true) {
377  /* Only update database entries if new raw data has been acquired */
378  /* Update timestamp */
379  mrc_state.lastBaseCellVoltageTimestamp = pCellVoltageBase->header.timestamp;
380 
381  /* Copy cell voltage base measurement values into validated database struct */
382  MRC_UpdateCellVoltageValidation(pCellVoltageBase, &mrc_tableCellVoltages);
383 
384  /* Set to true for following minimum, maximum and average calculation */
385  updatedValidatedVoltageDatbaseEntry = true;
386  }
387  }
388 
389  if (updatedValidatedVoltageDatbaseEntry == true) {
390  /* Calculate min/max/average cell voltages */
391  MRC_CalculateCellVoltageMinMaxAverage(&mrc_tableCellVoltages, &mrc_tableMinimumMaximumValues);
392 
393  /* Individual cell voltages validated and min/max/average calculated -> check voltage spread */
394  if (STD_NOT_OK == PL_CheckVoltageSpread(&mrc_tableCellVoltages, &mrc_tableMinimumMaximumValues)) {
395  /* Recalculate min/max/average cell voltages as at least one cell voltage has been detected as invalid */
396  MRC_CalculateCellVoltageMinMaxAverage(&mrc_tableCellVoltages, &mrc_tableMinimumMaximumValues);
397  }
398  }
399 
400  return updatedValidatedVoltageDatbaseEntry;
401 }

403 static bool MRC_ValidateCellTemperatureMeasurement(
404  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_TEMPERATURE_s *pCellTemperatureBase,
405  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_TEMPERATURE_s *pCellTemperatureRedundancy0) {
406  FAS_ASSERT(pCellTemperatureBase != NULL_PTR);
407  FAS_ASSERT(pCellTemperatureRedundancy0 != NULL_PTR);
408 
409  bool baseCelltemperatureUpdated = false;
410  bool useCelltemperatureRedundancy = false;
411  bool updatedValidatedTemperatureDatbaseEntry = false;
412 
413  bool baseCellTemperatureMeasurementTimeoutReached = true;
414  bool redundancy0CellTemperatureMeasurementTimeoutReached = true;
415 
416  /* Following decision will be undertaken:
417  *
418  * - Use redundancy only if timestamp of redundant database entry != 0
419  * - Perform redundant check if both timestamps have been updated
420  * - Add timeout and trigger error if timestamps have not been updated in the last XXXXms
421  * - If timeout reached and only one of the two redundant measurements has been updated use this measurement value
422  * but throw an error that one measurement has not been updated recently.
423  */
424 
425  /* -------------- Check if cell cell temperature redundant measurement is used ---------- */
426  /* Use redundant cell voltage measurements if measurement values have been acquired once */
427  useCelltemperatureRedundancy = DATA_DatabaseEntryUpdatedAtLeastOnce(pCellTemperatureRedundancy0->header);
428 
429  /* ----------------- Check timestamp of base measurements--------------- */
430  if (DATA_EntryUpdatedWithinInterval(pCellTemperatureBase->header, MRC_AFE_MEASUREMENT_PERIOD_TIMEOUT_ms) == true) {
431  baseCellTemperatureMeasurementTimeoutReached = false;
432  (void)DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_BASE_CELL_TEMPERATURE_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_EVENT_OK, DIAG_SYSTEM, 0u);
433  } else {
434  baseCellTemperatureMeasurementTimeoutReached = true;
435  /* Set error flag */
436  (void)DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_BASE_CELL_TEMPERATURE_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_EVENT_NOT_OK, DIAG_SYSTEM, 0u);
437  }
438  /* Check if base measurement values have been updated since last MRC */
439  if (mrc_state.lastBaseCelltemperatureTimestamp != pCellTemperatureBase->header.timestamp) {
440  baseCelltemperatureUpdated = true;
441  } else {
442  baseCelltemperatureUpdated = false;
443  }
444 
445  /* ----------------- Check timestamp of redundant measurements --------- */
446  if ((DATA_EntryUpdatedWithinInterval(pCellTemperatureRedundancy0->header, MRC_AFE_MEASUREMENT_PERIOD_TIMEOUT_ms) ==
447  false) &&
448  (useCelltemperatureRedundancy == true)) {
449  redundancy0CellTemperatureMeasurementTimeoutReached = true;
450  /* Set error flag */
451  (void)DIAG_Handler(
452  DIAG_ID_REDUNDANCY0_CELL_TEMPERATURE_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_EVENT_NOT_OK, DIAG_SYSTEM, 0u);
453  } else {
454  redundancy0CellTemperatureMeasurementTimeoutReached = false;
455  (void)DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_REDUNDANCY0_CELL_TEMPERATURE_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_EVENT_OK, DIAG_SYSTEM, 0u);
456  }
457 
458  /* ----------------- Validate cell temperatures ------------------------ */
459  if (useCelltemperatureRedundancy == true) {
460  bool redundancy0CelltemperatureUpdated = false;
461  /* Check if redundant measurement values have been updated since last MRC */
462  if (mrc_state.lastRedundancy0CelltemperatureTimestamp != pCellTemperatureRedundancy0->header.timestamp) {
463  redundancy0CelltemperatureUpdated = true;
464  } else {
465  redundancy0CelltemperatureUpdated = false;
466  }
467  /* Make sure cell voltage timestamps have been updated since last call */
468  if ((baseCelltemperatureUpdated == true) && (redundancy0CelltemperatureUpdated == true)) {
469  /* Update timestamp */
470  mrc_state.lastBaseCelltemperatureTimestamp = pCellTemperatureBase->header.timestamp;
471  mrc_state.lastRedundancy0CelltemperatureTimestamp = pCellTemperatureRedundancy0->header.timestamp;
472 
473  /* Validate cell temperatures */
474  MRC_ValidateCellTemperature(pCellTemperatureBase, pCellTemperatureRedundancy0, &mrc_tableCellTemperatures);
475  /* Set to true for following minimum, maximum and average calculation */
476  updatedValidatedTemperatureDatbaseEntry = true;
477  } else if ((baseCelltemperatureUpdated == true) || (redundancy0CelltemperatureUpdated == true)) {
478  /* At least one measurement has been updated */
479  if (baseCelltemperatureUpdated == true) {
480  /* Has redundant measurement timeout been reached? If yes, update. */
481  if (redundancy0CellTemperatureMeasurementTimeoutReached == true) {
482  /* Copy cell temperature base measurement values into validated database struct */
483  MRC_UpdateCellTemperatureValidation(pCellTemperatureBase, &mrc_tableCellTemperatures);
484  /* Set to true for following minimum, maximum and average calculation */
485  updatedValidatedTemperatureDatbaseEntry = true;
486  }
487  } else if (redundancy0CelltemperatureUpdated == true) {
488  /* Has base measurement timeout been reached? If yes, update. */
489  if (baseCellTemperatureMeasurementTimeoutReached == true) {
490  /* Copy cell temperature redundant measurement values into validated database struct */
491  MRC_UpdateCellTemperatureValidation(pCellTemperatureRedundancy0, &mrc_tableCellTemperatures);
492  /* Set to true for following minimum, maximum and average calculation */
493  updatedValidatedTemperatureDatbaseEntry = true;
494  }
495  } else {
496  FAS_ASSERT(FAS_TRAP);
497  }
498  } else {
499  /* No cell temperature measurement has been updated -> do nothing */
500  }
501  } else { /* useCelltemperatureRedundancy == true */
502  if (baseCelltemperatureUpdated == true) {
503  /* Only update database entries if new raw data has been acquired */
504  /* Update timestamp */
505  mrc_state.lastBaseCelltemperatureTimestamp = pCellTemperatureBase->header.timestamp;
506 
507  /* Copy cell temperature base measurement values into validated database struct */
508  MRC_UpdateCellTemperatureValidation(pCellTemperatureBase, &mrc_tableCellTemperatures);
509 
510  /* Set to true for following minimum, maximum and average calculation */
511  updatedValidatedTemperatureDatbaseEntry = true;
512  }
513  }
514 
515  if (updatedValidatedTemperatureDatbaseEntry == true) {
516  /* Calculate min/max/average cell temperatures */
517  MRC_CalculateCellTemperatureMinMaxAverage(&mrc_tableCellTemperatures, &mrc_tableMinimumMaximumValues);
518 
519  /* Individual cell temperatures validated and min/max/average calculated -> check temperature spread */
520  if (STD_NOT_OK == PL_CheckTemperatureSpread(&mrc_tableCellTemperatures, &mrc_tableMinimumMaximumValues)) {
521  /* Recalculate min/max/average temperatures as at least one temperature has been detected as invalid */
522  MRC_CalculateCellTemperatureMinMaxAverage(&mrc_tableCellTemperatures, &mrc_tableMinimumMaximumValues);
523  }
524  }
525 
526  return updatedValidatedTemperatureDatbaseEntry;
527 }

529 static void MRC_ValidateCurrentMeasurement(DATA_BLOCK_CURRENT_SENSOR_s *pTableCurrentSensor) {
530  FAS_ASSERT(pTableCurrentSensor != NULL_PTR);
531  int32_t packCurrent_mA = 0;
532 
533  /* Validate pack current. Will be invalidated if not all current measurement values are valid */
534  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidPackCurrent = 0u;
535 
536  /* Iterate over all strings to calculate pack current */
537  for (uint8_t s = 0u; s < BS_NR_OF_STRINGS; s++) {
538  /* Check timestamp of measurement */
539  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e noTimeout = MRC_MeasurementUpdatedRecently(
540  pTableCurrentSensor->timestampCurrent[s],
541  pTableCurrentSensor->previousTimestampCurrent[s],
542  MRC_CURRENT_MEASUREMENT_PERIOD_TIMEOUT_ms);
543  (void)DIAG_CheckEvent(noTimeout, DIAG_ID_CURRENT_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_STRING, s);
544 
545  if (noTimeout == STD_OK) {
546  /* Check if current entry has been updated since last call */
547  if (mrc_state.lastStringCurrentTimestamp[s] != pTableCurrentSensor->timestampCurrent[s]) {
548  mrc_state.lastStringCurrentTimestamp[s] = pTableCurrentSensor->timestampCurrent[s];
549  mrc_tablePackValues.stringCurrent_mA[s] = pTableCurrentSensor->current_mA[s];
550  if (pTableCurrentSensor->invalidCurrentMeasurement[s] == 0u) {

552  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringCurrent[s] = 0u;
553  (void)DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_CURRENT_MEASUREMENT_ERROR, DIAG_EVENT_OK, DIAG_STRING, s);
554  } else {
555  /* String current measurement invalid -> set invalid flag */
556  (void)DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_CURRENT_MEASUREMENT_ERROR, DIAG_EVENT_NOT_OK, DIAG_STRING, s);
557  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringCurrent[s] = 1u;
558  }
559  } else {
560  /* Nothing to do. Measurement has not been updated but still within timeout */
561  }
562  } else {
563  /* Measurement timeout reached -> set string current invalid */
564  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringCurrent[s] = 1u;
565  }
566 
567  if (mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringCurrent[s] == 0u) {
568  packCurrent_mA += mrc_tablePackValues.stringCurrent_mA[s];
569  } else {
570  /* One string current is invalid -> pack current cannot be correct.
571  * Set pack current invalid */
572  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidPackCurrent = 1u;
573  }
574  }
575  mrc_tablePackValues.packCurrent_mA = packCurrent_mA;

578 static void MRC_ValidateStringVoltageMeasurement(
579  DATA_BLOCK_CURRENT_SENSOR_s *pTableCurrentSensor,
580  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_VOLTAGE_s *pTableCellVoltage) {
581  /* Pointer validity check */
582  FAS_ASSERT(pTableCurrentSensor != NULL_PTR);
583  FAS_ASSERT(pTableCellVoltage != NULL_PTR);
584 
585  for (uint8_t s = 0u; s < BS_NR_OF_STRINGS; s++) {
586  /* Check timeout of current sensor measurement */
587  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e updatedMeasurement = MRC_MeasurementUpdatedRecently(
588  pTableCurrentSensor->timestampHighVoltage[s][0u],
589  pTableCurrentSensor->previousTimestampHighVoltage[s][0u],
590  MRC_CURRENT_SENSOR_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT_ms);
591  DIAG_CheckEvent(updatedMeasurement, DIAG_ID_CURRENT_SENSOR_V1_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_STRING, s);
592 
593  /* Perform plausibility check if AFE and new current sensor measurement is valid */
594  if ((updatedMeasurement == STD_OK) && (pTableCurrentSensor->invalidHighVoltageMeasurement[s][0u] == 0u) &&
595  (pTableCellVoltage->nrValidCellVoltages[s] == BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_STRING)) {
596  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e voltagePlausible =
597  PL_CheckStringVoltage(pTableCellVoltage->packVoltage_mV[s], pTableCurrentSensor->highVoltage_mV[s][0u]);
598  (void)DIAG_CheckEvent(voltagePlausible, DIAG_ID_PLAUSIBILITY_PACK_VOLTAGE, DIAG_STRING, s);
599 
600  /* Use current sensor measurement */ /* TODO: use really current sensor? Average of both? AFE measurement? */
601  mrc_tablePackValues.stringVoltage_mV[s] = pTableCurrentSensor->highVoltage_mV[s][0u];
602 
603  if (voltagePlausible == STD_OK) {
604  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringVoltage[s] = 0u;
605  } else {
606  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringVoltage[s] = 1u;
607  }
608  } else {
609  /* Plausibility check cannot be performed if we do not have valid
610  * values from AFE and current sensor measurement */
611  (void)DIAG_CheckEvent(STD_NOT_OK, DIAG_ID_PLAUSIBILITY_PACK_VOLTAGE, DIAG_STRING, s);
612 
613  if ((updatedMeasurement == STD_OK) && (pTableCurrentSensor->invalidHighVoltageMeasurement[s][0u] == 0u)) {
614  /* Current sensor measurement valid -> use this measurement */
615  mrc_tablePackValues.stringVoltage_mV[s] = pTableCurrentSensor->highVoltage_mV[s][0u];
616  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringVoltage[s] = 0u;
617  } else if (pTableCellVoltage->nrValidCellVoltages[s] == BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_STRING) {
618  /* AFE measurement valid -> use this measurement */
619  mrc_tablePackValues.stringVoltage_mV[s] = pTableCellVoltage->packVoltage_mV[s];
620  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringVoltage[s] = 0u;
621  } else {
622  /* AFE and current sensor measurement invalid -> try to construct
623  * a valid from the number of valid cell voltages and substitute
624  * invalid cell voltages with the average cell voltage. */
625  uint16_t numberInvalidCellVoltages =
626  (BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_STRING - pTableCellVoltage->nrValidCellVoltages[s]);
627 
628  mrc_tablePackValues.stringVoltage_mV[s] =
629  pTableCellVoltage->packVoltage_mV[s] +
630  (mrc_tableMinimumMaximumValues.averageCellVoltage_mV[s] * (int16_t)numberInvalidCellVoltages);
631 
632  /* Only use this as valid value if not more than five cell voltages are invalid */
633  if (numberInvalidCellVoltages > MRC_ALLOWED_NUMBER_OF_INVALID_CELL_VOLTAGES) {
634  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringVoltage[s] = 1u;
635  } else {
636  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringVoltage[s] = 0u;
637  }
638  }
639  }
640  }

645  int8_t numberOfValidStringVoltages = 0;
646  uint8_t numberOfConnectedStrings = BMS_GetNumberOfConnectedStrings();

718 static void MRC_ValidatePowerMeasurement(DATA_BLOCK_CURRENT_SENSOR_s *pTableCurrentSensor) {
719  FAS_ASSERT(pTableCurrentSensor != NULL_PTR);
720  bool calculatePower = false;
721  int32_t packPower_W = 0;
722 
723  /* Validate pack power. Will be invalidated if not all power measurement values are valid */
724  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidPackPower = 0u;
725 
726  for (uint8_t s = 0u; s < BS_NR_OF_STRINGS; s++) {
727  /* Check timeout of current sensor measurement */
728  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e noTimeout = MRC_MeasurementUpdatedRecently(
729  pTableCurrentSensor->timestampPower[s],
730  pTableCurrentSensor->previousTimestampPower[s],
731  MRC_CURRENT_SENSOR_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT_ms);
732  DIAG_CheckEvent(noTimeout, DIAG_ID_CURRENT_SENSOR_POWER_MEASUREMENT_TIMEOUT, DIAG_STRING, s);
733 
734  if (noTimeout == STD_OK) {
735  /* Check if current sensor measurement has been updated */
736  if (pTableCurrentSensor->timestampPower[s] != mrc_state.lastStringPowerTimestamp[s]) {
737  mrc_state.lastStringPowerTimestamp[s] = pTableCurrentSensor->timestampPower[s];
738  /* Check if measurement is valid */
739  if (pTableCurrentSensor->invalidPowerMeasurement[s] == 0u) {
740  mrc_tablePackValues.stringPower_W[s] = pTableCurrentSensor->power_W[s];
741  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringPower[s] = 0u;
742  } else {
743  /* Measurement has been updated but value is invalid -> calculate from current and string voltage */
744  calculatePower = true;
745  /* TODO: do we want to calculate values by hand if we are within time limit but value is invalid? */
746  }
747  } else {
748  /* Nothing to do. Measurement has not been updated but still within timeout */
749  }
750  } else {
751  /* Timeout reached. Set invalid flag */
752  calculatePower = true;
753  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringPower[s] = 1u;
754  }
755  if ((calculatePower == true) && (mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringCurrent[s] == 0u) &&
756  (mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringVoltage[s] == 0u)) {
757  /* Power measurement is invalid, but current and string voltage measurement are valid */
758  int64_t stringPower_W =
759  ((mrc_tablePackValues.stringCurrent_mA[s] * mrc_tablePackValues.stringVoltage_mV[s]) /
760  (UNIT_CONVERSION_FACTOR_1000_INTEGER * /* convert: mV -> V */
761  UNIT_CONVERSION_FACTOR_1000_INTEGER)); /* convert: mA -> A */
762  mrc_tablePackValues.stringPower_W[s] = (int32_t)stringPower_W;
763  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringPower[s] = 0u;
764  }
765  if (mrc_tablePackValues.invalidStringPower[s] == 0u) {
766  packPower_W += mrc_tablePackValues.stringPower_W[s];
767  DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_POWER_MEASUREMENT_ERROR, DIAG_EVENT_OK, DIAG_STRING, s);
768  } else {
769  /* One string power is invalid -> pack power cannot be correct.
770  * Set pack power invalid */
771  mrc_tablePackValues.invalidPackPower = 1u;
772  DIAG_Handler(DIAG_ID_POWER_MEASUREMENT_ERROR, DIAG_EVENT_NOT_OK, DIAG_STRING, s);
773  }
774  }
775  mrc_tablePackValues.packPower_W = packPower_W;
776 }

778 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e MRC_CalculateCellVoltageMinMaxAverage(
779  const DATA_BLOCK_CELL_VOLTAGE_s *const pValidatedVoltages,
780  DATA_BLOCK_MIN_MAX_s *pMinMaxAverageValues) {
781  /* Pointer validity check */
782  FAS_ASSERT(pValidatedVoltages != NULL_PTR);
783  FAS_ASSERT(pMinMaxAverageValues != NULL_PTR);
784 
785  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e retval = STD_OK;
786 
787  for (uint8_t s = 0u; s < BS_NR_OF_STRINGS; s++) {
788  uint16_t nrValidCellVoltages = 0u;
789  int16_t min = INT16_MAX;
790  int16_t max = INT16_MIN;
791  int32_t sum = 0;
792  uint16_t moduleNumberMinimum = 0u;
793  uint16_t cellNumberMinimum = 0u;
794  uint16_t moduleNumberMaximum = 0u;
795  uint16_t cellNumberMaximum = 0u;
796  /* Iterate over all cells in each string */
797  for (uint8_t m = 0u; m < BS_NR_OF_MODULES_PER_STRING; m++) {
798  for (uint8_t c = 0u; c < BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE; c++) {
799  if ((pValidatedVoltages->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] & (0x01u << c)) == 0u) {
800  /* Cell voltage is valid -> use this voltage for subsequent calculations */
801  nrValidCellVoltages++;
802  sum += pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c];
803 
804  if (pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c] < min) {
805  min = pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c];
806  moduleNumberMinimum = m;
807  cellNumberMinimum = c;
808  }
809  if (pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c] > max) {
810  max = pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c];
811  moduleNumberMaximum = m;
812  cellNumberMaximum = c;
813  }
814  }
815  }
816  }
817  pMinMaxAverageValues->minimumCellVoltage_mV[s] = min;
818  pMinMaxAverageValues->nrCellMinimumCellVoltage[s] = cellNumberMinimum;
819  pMinMaxAverageValues->nrModuleMinimumCellVoltage[s] = moduleNumberMinimum;
820  pMinMaxAverageValues->maximumCellVoltage_mV[s] = max;
821  pMinMaxAverageValues->nrCellMaximumCellVoltage[s] = cellNumberMaximum;
822  pMinMaxAverageValues->nrModuleMaximumCellVoltage[s] = moduleNumberMaximum;
823  pMinMaxAverageValues->validMeasuredCellVoltages[s] = nrValidCellVoltages;
824 
825  /* Prevent division by 0, if all cell voltages are invalid */
826  if (nrValidCellVoltages > 0u) {
827  pMinMaxAverageValues->averageCellVoltage_mV[s] = (int16_t)(sum / (int32_t)nrValidCellVoltages);
828  } else {
829  pMinMaxAverageValues->averageCellVoltage_mV[s] = 0;
830  retval = STD_NOT_OK;
831  }
832  }
833  return retval;
834 }

899 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e MRC_ValidateCellVoltage(
900  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_VOLTAGE_s *pCellVoltageBase,
901  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_VOLTAGE_s *pCellVoltageRedundancy0,
902  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_VOLTAGE_s *pValidatedVoltages) {
903  /* Pointer validity check */
904  FAS_ASSERT(pCellVoltageBase != NULL_PTR);
905  FAS_ASSERT(pCellVoltageRedundancy0 != NULL_PTR);
906  FAS_ASSERT(pValidatedVoltages != NULL_PTR);
907 
908  uint16_t numberValidMeasurements = 0u;
909  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e noPlausibilityIssueDetected = STD_OK; /* Flag if implausible value detected */
910  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e retval = STD_OK;
911 
912  /* Iterate over all cell measurements */
913  for (uint8_t s = 0u; s < BS_NR_OF_STRINGS; s++) {
914  int32_t sum = 0;
915  for (uint8_t m = 0; m < BS_NR_OF_MODULES_PER_STRING; m++) {
916  for (uint8_t c = 0; c < BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE; c++) {
917  if (((pCellVoltageBase->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] & (1u << c)) == 0u) &&
918  ((pCellVoltageRedundancy0->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] & (1u << c)) == 0u)) {
919  /* Check if cell voltage of base AND redundant measurement is valid -> do plausibility check */
920  if (STD_OK ==
921  PL_CheckCellVoltage(
922  pCellVoltageBase->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c],
923  pCellVoltageRedundancy0->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c],
924  &pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c])) {
925  /* Clear valid flag */
926  pValidatedVoltages->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] = pValidatedVoltages->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] &
927  (~(1u << c));
928  numberValidMeasurements++;
929  sum += pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c];
930  } else {
931  /* Set invalid flag */
932  noPlausibilityIssueDetected = STD_NOT_OK;
933  pValidatedVoltages->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] |= (1u << c);
934  /* Set return value to #STD_NOT_OK as not all cell voltages have a valid measurement value */
935  retval = STD_NOT_OK;
936  }
937  } else if ((pCellVoltageBase->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] & (1u << c)) == 0u) {
938  /* Only base measurement value is valid -> use this voltage without further plausibility checks */
939  pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c] =
940  pCellVoltageBase->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c];
941  /* Reset valid flag */
942  pValidatedVoltages->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] = pValidatedVoltages->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] &
943  (~(1u << c));
944  numberValidMeasurements++;
945  sum += pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c];
946  } else if ((pCellVoltageRedundancy0->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] & (1u << c)) == 0u) {
947  /* Only redundant measurement value is valid -> use this voltage without further plausibility checks */
948  pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c] =
949  pCellVoltageRedundancy0->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c];
950  /* Reset valid flag */
951  pValidatedVoltages->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] = pValidatedVoltages->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] &
952  (~(1u << c));
953  numberValidMeasurements++;
954  sum += pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c];
955  } else {
956  /* Both, base and redundant measurement value are invalid */
957  /* Save average cell voltage value of base and redundant */
958  pValidatedVoltages->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c] =
959  (pCellVoltageBase->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c] +
960  pCellVoltageRedundancy0->cellVoltage_mV[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + c]) /
961  2u;
962  /* Set invalid flag */
963  pValidatedVoltages->invalidCellVoltage[s][m] |= (1u << c);
964  /* Set return value to #STD_NOT_OK as not all cell voltages have a valid measurement value */
965  retval = STD_NOT_OK;
966  }
967  }
968  }
969  pValidatedVoltages->nrValidCellVoltages[s] = numberValidMeasurements;
970  pValidatedVoltages->packVoltage_mV[s] = sum;
971  numberValidMeasurements = 0u; /* Reset counter for next string */
972 
973  (void)DIAG_CheckEvent(noPlausibilityIssueDetected, DIAG_ID_PLAUSIBILITY_CELL_VOLTAGE, DIAG_STRING, s);
974  noPlausibilityIssueDetected = STD_OK; /* Reset flag for next string */
975  }
976  return retval;

996 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e MRC_ValidateCellTemperature(
997  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_TEMPERATURE_s *pCelltemperatureBase,
998  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_TEMPERATURE_s *pCelltemperatureRedundancy0,
999  DATA_BLOCK_CELL_TEMPERATURE_s *pValidatedTemperatures) {
1000  /* Pointer validity check */
1001  FAS_ASSERT(pCelltemperatureBase != NULL_PTR);
1002  FAS_ASSERT(pCelltemperatureRedundancy0 != NULL_PTR);
1003  FAS_ASSERT(pValidatedTemperatures != NULL_PTR);
1004 
1005  uint16_t numberValidMeasurements = 0u;
1006  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e noPlausibilityIssueDetected = STD_OK; /* Flag if implausible value detected */
1007  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e retval = STD_OK;
1008 
1009  /* Iterate over all cell measurements */
1010  for (uint8_t s = 0u; s < BS_NR_OF_STRINGS; s++) {
1011  for (uint8_t m = 0u; m < BS_NR_OF_MODULES_PER_STRING; m++) {
1012  for (uint8_t c = 0u; c < BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE; c++) {
1013  if (((pCelltemperatureBase->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] & (1u << c)) == 0u) &&
1014  ((pCelltemperatureRedundancy0->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] & (1u << c)) == 0u)) {
1015  /* Check if cell voltage of base AND redundant measurement is valid -> do plausibility check */
1016  if (STD_OK ==
1017  PL_CheckCelltemperature(
1018  pCelltemperatureBase->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c],
1019  pCelltemperatureRedundancy0
1020  ->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c],
1021  &pValidatedTemperatures
1022  ->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c])) {
1023  /* Clear valid flag */
1024  pValidatedTemperatures->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] =
1025  pValidatedTemperatures->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] & (~(1u << c));
1026  numberValidMeasurements++;
1027  } else {
1028  /* Set invalid flag */
1029  noPlausibilityIssueDetected = STD_NOT_OK;
1030  pValidatedTemperatures->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] |= (1u << c);
1031  /* Set return value to #STD_NOT_OK as not all cell temperatures have a valid measurement value */
1032  retval = STD_NOT_OK;
1033  }
1034  } else if ((pCelltemperatureBase->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] & (1u << c)) == 0u) {
1035  /* Only base measurement value is valid -> use this temperature without further plausibility checks */
1036  pValidatedTemperatures->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c] =
1037  pCelltemperatureBase->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c];
1038  /* Reset valid flag */
1039  pValidatedTemperatures->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] =
1040  pValidatedTemperatures->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] & (~(1u << c));
1041  numberValidMeasurements++;
1042  } else if ((pCelltemperatureRedundancy0->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] & (1u << c)) == 0u) {
1043  /* Only redundant measurement value is valid -> use this temperature without further plausibility checks */
1044  pValidatedTemperatures->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c] =
1045  pCelltemperatureRedundancy0
1046  ->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c];
1047  /* Reset valid flag */
1048  pValidatedTemperatures->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] =
1049  pValidatedTemperatures->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] & (~(1u << c));
1050  numberValidMeasurements++;
1051  } else {
1052  /* Both, base and redundant measurement value are invalid */
1053  /* Save average cell voltage value of base and redundant */
1054  pValidatedTemperatures->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c] =
1055  (pCelltemperatureBase->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c] +
1056  pCelltemperatureRedundancy0
1057  ->cellTemperature_ddegC[s][(m * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + c]) /
1058  2u;
1059  /* Set invalid flag */
1060  pValidatedTemperatures->invalidCellTemperature[s][m] |= (1u << c);
1061  /* Set return value to #STD_NOT_OK as not all cell temperatures have a valid measurement value */
1062  retval = STD_NOT_OK;
1063  }
1064  }
1065  }
1066  pValidatedTemperatures->nrValidTemperatures[s] = numberValidMeasurements;
1067  numberValidMeasurements = 0u; /* Reset counter for next string */
1068 
1069  (void)DIAG_CheckEvent(noPlausibilityIssueDetected, DIAG_ID_PLAUSIBILITY_CELL_TEMP, DIAG_STRING, s);
1070  noPlausibilityIssueDetected = STD_OK; /* Reset flag for next string */
1071  }
1072 
1073  return retval;
1074 }
